-- #556: the BINARY spelling of the same overflow (2^62+1).  Pinned separately
-- from the hex fixture because the bound is per-base (binary's admissible digit
-- count is 63, hex's is 16) — a fix validated only on hex would not prove this.
-- Self-hosted reference: integer literal too large for Int (max magnitude 2^62)
x = 0b100000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000001
